Embodiments of the invention will now be described by way of example with reference to the accompanying drawings in which:
Figure 1 shows a longitudinal cross-section through a ducted fan gas turbine engine;
Figure 2 shows a typical abradable liner tip rub profile;
Figure 3 shows an axial root blade on the left and circumferential root blade on the right;
Figure 4 shows schematically three tilt positions in which a blade can rest relative to a disc;
Figure 5 shows schematically (a) a ground profile of two blades resting in two positions during the grinding process, and (b) the ground blades with resting positions swapped during a period of use;
Figure 6 shows schematically a rearwards directed view of blade tip of a blade with an axial root for different levels of tilt;
Figure 7 shows schematically (a) a side view of a root of a blade loaded in an axial slot of a disc, (b) a bottom view of the root of the blade loaded in the axial slot, and (c) a side view of a blade loaded in a circumferential slot of a disc; and
Figure 8 shows schematically (a) a bottom view of the roots of two neighbouring blades loaded in respective axial slots formed in a rim of a disc, and (b) a side view of a blade loaded in a circumferential slot of a disc.
